******
[2] Broccoli, eastern England
Date: Fri 10 Feb 2017
Source: HorticultureWeek [edited]
http://www.hortweek.com/alert-light-leaf-spot/edibles/article/1423926


Light leaf spot has been reported in the East of England on broccoli and is active in oilseed rape crops. Early symptoms can be difficult to diagnose. Incubation of plants in a plastic bag can help as white spore droplets can form around the lesion.

--
